metadata.name: CONNECT D-ajop1j021 #28
metadata.description:
※Due to the characteristics of the work, the output will vary depending on the screen size.
If the screen size is the same, the output will be the same.
Thumbnail images are 800px x 800px.

First, the base color is placed, then random symbols (letters) are placed in a draw() loop process.
Then, specific symbol are linked to each other by their x,y color.

Red, Blue, Yellow, and Black colors are references to the untitled print work by Hiroshi Kawano, and works by Mondrian. I started this work by imitating and looking at their work.

This work is the beginning of my exploration of the relationship between weaving, computers, and generation, and I plan to produce the CONNECT series using similar techniques.

Please feel free to contact me if you have any inquiries.

Artwork by hasaqui, @hasaqui.
Made with p5js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: contrapuntos #679
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Smoke #55
metadata.description:
Inspired by the hot weather of the city.
Made in August 2022, Milano, Italy.

5 visible Features:
-Mood: tender, bleed, icecream, summer in Milano, evening, futurepunk, acid, love
-Size: small, regular, big
-Density: low, moderate, high, very high
-Speed: slow, moderate, fast
-Emissions: from 2 to 9

Some of the features are very rare, others less, some more common.

The design is being optimized to render at different speeds depending on the size of the window. The smaller the size, the faster the render and lower the detail, viceversa bigger the size, slower the render and higher the detail.
The moire effect of lines that are making the shades of the artwork will look thick with a low resolution, and become finer and more detailed the higher the resolution. You can use this feature to create quick previews or to save very Hi-Resolution images.
To save an image with the size of the window press S once the image is fully rendered.
The fx(hash) thumbnail is saved at 1425px x 1900px.
To save a Hi-Resolution image 3000px x 4000px press H and wait, the page will reload and start to render. Please be patient.

Built using p5js, published under CC-BY-NC-4.0 license.

Once the collection will be fully minted, the variations button will be disabled.

metadata.name: Dencity #182
metadata.description:
Dencity is a generative art project inspired by aerial views of cities with a high density of buildings. Its perspective effect, its perfectly imprecise lines, its subtle textures and its very advanced level of detail give it the appearance of a hand-drawn work.

Behind the visible art (the image) hides another form of art, an extremely complex algorithm capable of calculating and drawing in 2D each variation of the Dencity project. To draw a variation, the algorithm notably takes around 3,000,000 to 20,000,000 random decisions based on the hash of the mint and draws around 800,000 to 4,000,000 lines to create all the strokes and texture effects.

Made with ❤️, code and p5js.

metadata.name: Multidimensional Maximalism #169
metadata.description:
Multidimensional Maximalism is my learning experience with layering and composition.

Using the Cellular Automaton algorithm from "Gen., Machina" we create multiple dimensions of life. Each with it's own unique evolution and structure. Like petri dishes in a lab. We then use different compositional elements to explore these dimensions.

100% code - as always.

Available overlays
--
* Lasers (drawing inspiration from The Harvest by Per Kristian Stoveland)
* Circleblend
* Drops
* Lenses
* Squares
* Crazysquares
* Waves
* Tesseract (drawing inspiration from the awesome Tesseract collection by Studio Yorktown)
* None (unlucky you)

Controls (in live view):
--
Press [1-9] to set the export scale ratio
Press [s] to save a high resolution image [ resolution x scale ]

enjoy.

metadata.name: amongst the straight and narrow #66
metadata.description:
This project continues my exploration of attempting to simulate drawing with markers, this time on top of a more textured fabric-like surface. The marks themselves can range from highly ordered to highly disordered, with various intermediate states.

---

So let us wander far,
Amongst the straight and narrow.
For it is in the detours,
That we find our souls' marrow.

metadata.name: Lands #47
metadata.description:
Lands are a group of artworks creating a minimalist and abstract satellite view. The earth is changing, more and more, day after day, the satellite views are a great proof of that. Stay aware and be careful is important.

I wanted to representing something real, linked with my values, and keep a beautiful composition and colors harmony.  I worked with a new fresh touch for the colors management.

The size, position and frequency of the pieces are generated for each token, along with the color theme. 

Features : 
- piecesCount : the number of circles and rectangles.
- glitchLinesCount :  the number of lines behind the shapes.
- MultipleGlitchDirections : if the directions of the lines behind are just horizontal or vertical, or both (10% of chance to have only one direction) .

 Handmade by code with Javascript, made with fragment.tools
 Quentin Hocdé, Brussels (Belgium), 2023.
